                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-255-defend1397 t18270531-255-deflabel1372"></join>. On the 9th of May, at twelve o'clock, he took out his beer, and returned for some gin - I asked him to account for his beer - he said he would rather take out the two o'clock beer first - he did so - he came back, and asked for change for a sovereign to take for the gin - I gave him half-a-sovereign, two half-crowns, and four shillings, to take to Mr. Reynolds - he did not return - he was taken on the 11th, and said he had lost the sovereign - he had taken his clothes away before that.</p>
